cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper deals with deep neural networks and their optimization for training and inference. Specifically, it focuses on convolutional neural networks and their parameter sparsity, as well as runtime feature map usage. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as these categories are also relevant to the optimization of deep neural networks.
